1
00:02:11,670 --> 00:02:15,430
Run for Young

2
00:02:17,090 --> 00:02:17,690
Big Mouth.

3
00:02:18,490 --> 00:02:20,530
Doggo is a little off these days.

4
00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:22,890
For more than ten years,

5
00:02:23,130 --> 00:02:24,530
it seems that he has never been normal.

6
00:02:24,690 --> 00:02:25,770
That's right.

7
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:27,690
You're the same!

8
00:02:27,690 --> 00:02:28,690
Why me now?

9
00:02:30,690 --> 00:02:31,530
That day,

10
00:02:31,530 --> 00:02:32,810
he shouted that he was in love.

11
00:02:33,450 --> 00:02:34,850
So, he meant Anran, right?

12
00:02:37,690 --> 00:02:38,490
Unexpectedly,

13
00:02:39,050 --> 00:02:39,730
Anran and Qin

14
00:02:39,730 --> 00:02:41,530
seem to have a story.

15
00:02:42,090 --> 00:02:43,810
It's complicated, Teaty.

16
00:02:43,850 --> 00:02:44,810
What do you mean, Big Mouth?

17
00:02:45,130 --> 00:02:45,810
Look.

18
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:48,050
Ma Tian likes Hercules Jiao.

19
00:02:48,610 --> 00:02:50,129
Hercules Jiao likes Doggo.

20
00:02:51,009 --> 00:02:52,210
Doggo likes Anran.

21
00:02:52,770 --> 00:02:54,410
Anran turns out to like Liu Wenqin!

22
00:02:55,130 --> 00:02:56,130
What?

23
00:02:56,930 --> 00:02:58,330
It's so complicated!

24
00:02:58,330 --> 00:02:59,330
How did you tell?

25
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:01,530
Of course because I'm smart.

26
00:03:01,810 --> 00:03:03,530
Then in such a complicated situation,

27
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:05,410
how can I date Chen Yuanyuan?

28
00:03:06,770 --> 00:03:07,370
Teaty.

29
00:03:07,890 --> 00:03:09,690
The complicated relationship I talked about

30
00:03:10,210 --> 00:03:12,570
has nothing to do with Chen Yuanyuan, alright?

31
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:14,250
Right.

32
00:03:15,210 --> 00:03:16,050
Then what to do?

33
00:03:17,610 --> 00:03:19,050
This is a youth TV show, okay?

34
00:03:20,330 --> 00:03:22,410
There are always regrets in youth.

35
00:03:23,290 --> 00:03:24,130
The director said

36
00:03:24,130 --> 00:03:26,010
it'd upgrade the level in this way.

37
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:28,810
What is my regret then?

38
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:30,690
It's yet to come.

39
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:31,930
You're just a supporting actor!

40
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:34,290
But I don't feel getting involved.

41
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:36,330
Two male leads.

42
00:03:36,330 --> 00:03:37,410
Two female leads.

43
00:03:37,730 --> 00:03:39,690
It's normal that we are left behind.

44
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:41,650
Supporting roles should

45
00:03:41,650 --> 00:03:42,610
also have highlights.

46
00:03:43,770 --> 00:03:45,530
It's yet to come.

47
00:03:45,570 --> 00:03:46,370
How much longer?

48
00:03:48,370 --> 00:03:49,410
At least the sixth episode.

49
00:03:50,090 --> 00:03:50,690
How do you know?

50
00:03:51,210 --> 00:03:52,250
You didn't read the script!

51
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:57,690
Episode 5 Can Sea Shrimp and River Shrimp Live Together?

52
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:05,290
Doggo.

53
00:04:07,050 --> 00:04:08,730
Actually, I should have told you earlier

54
00:04:09,770 --> 00:04:10,570
that I'm looking for him.

55
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:14,050
Actually, I already knew that.

56
00:04:19,010 --> 00:04:20,410
The person that Qin always mentioned

57
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:23,090
back then was you.

58
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:29,730
Anran, hurry up!

59
00:04:31,090 --> 00:04:31,930
Let's go.

60
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:33,570
Let's go home. I'm so sleepy.

61
00:04:34,130 --> 00:04:36,050
SARS finally ended.

62
00:04:36,530 --> 00:04:38,530
I haven't seen so many people in the street for ages!

63
00:04:40,010 --> 00:04:40,730
Look.

64
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:03,330
Girl.

65
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:04,370
Why are you wearing a mask?

66
00:05:04,490 --> 00:05:05,530
None of your business!

67
00:05:05,690 --> 00:05:06,810
Take it off and show your face.

68
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:09,650
Don't go! Take it off and show your face.

69
00:05:44,650 --> 00:05:45,370
What?

70
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:46,850
Don't embarrass yourself.

71
00:05:46,850 --> 00:05:47,530
What does it mean?

72
00:05:47,770 --> 00:05:48,410
Say it again!

73
00:05:48,650 --> 00:05:49,290
What!

74
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:53,530
Don't you pretend!

75
00:05:54,010 --> 00:05:54,650
What?

76
00:05:54,650 --> 00:05:55,810
You beat him because you lost?

77
00:05:56,050 --> 00:05:56,650
What did you say?

78
00:05:57,370 --> 00:05:58,130
Say it again!

79
00:05:58,730 --> 00:05:59,350
Say it again!

80
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:10,570
Are you okay?

81
00:07:11,930 --> 00:07:12,970
They are too weak.

82
00:07:13,890 --> 00:07:14,930
What's there to see?

83
00:07:15,850 --> 00:07:16,850
Don't do this next time.

84
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:18,650
I haven't seen it before.

85
00:07:20,210 --> 00:07:21,450
SARS is over.

86
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:22,650
Why are you still wearing a mask?

87
00:07:50,530 --> 00:07:51,690
Are you from Yucai Middle School?

88
00:07:52,450 --> 00:07:53,290
How do you know that?

89
00:08:00,130 --> 00:08:01,410
It's written there...

90
00:08:06,850 --> 00:08:07,810
It's too late.

91
00:08:07,850 --> 00:08:08,970
Go home now.

92
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:15,490
What's your name?

93
00:08:16,330 --> 00:08:16,930
My name is

94
00:08:18,210 --> 00:08:19,010
Liu Wenqin.

95
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:48,330
There is a match with other schools
in the basketball gym today.

96
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:48,970
Let's go and watch.

97
00:08:49,370 --> 00:08:50,810
I don't like basketball.

98
00:08:51,010 --> 00:08:52,770
I don't like it, either.

99
00:08:53,050 --> 00:08:54,210
But there are handsome guys!

100
00:08:55,170 --> 00:08:56,250
We're so young.

101
00:08:56,330 --> 00:08:57,250
Why look for handsome guys?

102
00:08:57,490 --> 00:08:59,570
Guys are handsome when they're young!

103
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:00,690
Go.

104
00:09:01,170 --> 00:09:01,890
Let's go.

105
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:14,690
What's so good about this?

106
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:22,330
Boring.

107
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:25,730
Look! That Number Five is amazing.

108
00:09:26,370 --> 00:09:27,490
I don't like this.

109
00:09:28,850 --> 00:09:30,570
Come on, Liu Wenqin!

110
00:10:32,850 --> 00:10:34,450
Sorry.

111
00:10:34,450 --> 00:10:35,250
She doesn't know the rules.

112
00:10:35,690 --> 00:10:37,370
She thought it was our school.

113
00:10:45,090 --> 00:10:46,650
When is the next match?

114
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:48,330
There's another one on Friday.

115
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:50,690
But it will be in the Jiefangbei Middle School.

116
00:10:51,370 --> 00:10:53,610
If we lose this game, we will be eliminated.

117
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:57,530
Today, we are going to learn an article

118
00:10:57,690 --> 00:11:00,690
"The Sichuan Road" written by Li Bai.

119
00:11:01,130 --> 00:11:02,810
Actually, we have learned

120
00:11:02,810 --> 00:11:04,010
about Li Bai, the poet.

121
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:07,610
Let's go together.

122
00:11:07,690 --> 00:11:08,290
No.

123
00:11:10,770 --> 00:11:13,330
For Li Bai, where there was wine,

124
00:11:13,410 --> 00:11:14,730
that would be his hometown.

125
00:11:15,170 --> 00:11:16,090
Yes, Anran?

126
00:11:16,490 --> 00:11:18,250
Teacher, I want to use the bathroom.

127
00:11:18,610 --> 00:11:19,270
Go ahead.

128
00:12:09,050 --> 00:12:11,750
CHONGQING JIEFANGBEI MIDDLE SCHOOL

129
00:12:18,650 --> 00:12:19,250
What are you doing?

130
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:21,810
I went home just now.

131
00:12:22,530 --> 00:12:23,210
Your school uniform?

132
00:12:23,890 --> 00:12:25,330
I left it at home.

133
00:12:26,410 --> 00:12:27,450
Did you ask for leave?

134
00:12:27,730 --> 00:12:28,410
Yes.

135
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:01,330
Liu Wenqin.

136
00:13:01,570 --> 00:13:03,250
Come on!

137
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:39,210
I saw you just now.

138
00:13:39,850 --> 00:13:41,290
My friend is on the team.

139
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:42,410
So I came to watch it.

140
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:43,170
Who?

141
00:13:47,290 --> 00:13:47,930
Him!

142
00:13:48,290 --> 00:13:48,930
Doggo?

143
00:13:49,330 --> 00:13:51,050
He never said he had a friend from Yucai.

144
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:52,450
Doggo...

145
00:13:54,250 --> 00:13:54,890
Got it.

146
00:14:02,290 --> 00:14:02,910
What?

147
00:14:15,370 --> 00:14:16,410
If you don't deal with your twisted ankle,

148
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,050
it will swell badly tomorrow.

149
00:14:26,210 --> 00:14:27,250
What's your name?

150
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:28,970
Li Anran.

151
00:15:40,690 --> 00:15:42,810
One, two, three, come on!

152
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:43,890
Assemble!

153
00:15:45,090 --> 00:15:45,730
Wenqin.

154
00:15:46,810 --> 00:15:48,250
The trial on the 24th.

155
00:15:48,770 --> 00:15:49,930
You must play well.

156
00:15:50,610 --> 00:15:52,370
The key universities will come to select people.

157
00:15:53,690 --> 00:15:55,010
With your talent,

158
00:15:55,290 --> 00:15:56,690
you may be recommended for admission.

159
00:15:57,930 --> 00:15:59,370
Don't miss this opportunity.

160
00:16:15,370 --> 00:16:17,170
Are you going to sneak out again?

161
00:16:17,930 --> 00:16:19,530
Today is the semi-final.

162
00:16:19,610 --> 00:16:20,770
I have to go.

163
00:16:22,410 --> 00:16:24,290
Will the teacher let you go?

164
00:16:25,210 --> 00:16:25,850
I don't know.

165
00:16:26,490 --> 00:16:27,370
It depends on luck.

166
00:16:27,850 --> 00:16:28,810
Let me help you this time.

167
00:16:29,410 --> 00:16:30,850
Next time, you have to find a way.

168
00:16:31,650 --> 00:16:32,810
How will you help me?

169
00:16:34,370 --> 00:16:35,050
Ouch!

170
00:16:35,570 --> 00:16:36,290
What's the matter?

171
00:16:36,770 --> 00:16:38,650
Teacher, s-she fainted.

172
00:16:38,770 --> 00:16:40,530
Anran, please take her to the infirmary now.

173
00:16:40,570 --> 00:16:41,650
You two sit down.

174
00:16:41,810 --> 00:16:42,730
Please keep studying.

175
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:44,170
What's the matter?

176
00:16:44,810 --> 00:16:45,650
I feel dizzy.

177
00:16:46,450 --> 00:16:47,170
Hurry.

178
00:16:49,650 --> 00:16:50,250
Lie down.

179
00:16:50,370 --> 00:16:51,370
Let me check for you.

180
00:16:51,610 --> 00:16:52,490
Go ahead. Come on.

181
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:11,690
Climb back.

182
00:17:14,370 --> 00:17:15,130
Climb back!

183
00:17:44,610 --> 00:17:46,169
What will you do when you get home?

184
00:17:47,449 --> 00:17:48,209
I don't know.

185
00:17:54,330 --> 00:17:55,050
Huh?

186
00:18:05,169 --> 00:18:06,689
Why are you here today?

187
00:18:08,970 --> 00:18:10,090
The game ended early.

188
00:18:10,370 --> 00:18:11,530
So I came with my friends.

189
00:18:12,370 --> 00:18:13,530
What are you doing here?

190
00:18:19,290 --> 00:18:20,330
Let me buy you dinner, okay?

191
00:18:22,690 --> 00:18:23,450
What do you say?

192
00:18:23,890 --> 00:18:24,810
Why?

193
00:18:27,530 --> 00:18:28,890
I'll be recommended to a university.

194
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:30,050
Really?

195
00:18:30,410 --> 00:18:31,890
Then let's eat Pizza Hut.

196
00:18:32,650 --> 00:18:33,410
What is Pizza Hut?

197
00:18:33,650 --> 00:18:34,490
A pizza restaurant.

198
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:36,730
It's a kind of cake.

199
00:18:36,970 --> 00:18:38,210
Chicken wings.

200
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:39,370
French fries.

201
00:18:40,290 --> 00:18:41,250
Grilled chicken skewer.

202
00:18:41,730 --> 00:18:43,170
Phoenix-tailed prawn.

203
00:18:44,010 --> 00:18:45,490
And a bacon pizza.

204
00:18:45,890 --> 00:18:47,250
Fruit salad.

205
00:18:49,010 --> 00:18:49,730
Won't you order?

206
00:18:51,530 --> 00:18:52,530
I just finished playing.

207
00:18:53,130 --> 00:18:54,690
I'm a bit tired, no appetite, not hungry.

208
00:18:55,890 --> 00:18:57,170
That's all for now.

209
00:18:57,530 --> 00:18:58,190
Okay.

210
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:02,410
That's 328 yuan in total.

211
00:19:11,370 --> 00:19:12,330
Three hundred and five.

212
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:12,950
Thank you.

213
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:22,250
Won't you eat?

214
00:19:24,930 --> 00:19:25,530
I'm not hungry.

215
00:19:26,890 --> 00:19:27,530
Have a piece.

216
00:19:29,810 --> 00:19:30,530
It's delicious.

217
00:19:43,530 --> 00:19:44,170
Is it?

218
00:19:45,130 --> 00:19:45,810
Yes.

219
00:19:55,810 --> 00:19:57,370
Hello, what can I help you?

220
00:19:58,130 --> 00:19:59,290
It's fine. I'm just browsing.

221
00:19:59,690 --> 00:20:01,490
This is the latest James II.

222
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:02,930
The design of its sole

223
00:20:02,930 --> 00:20:03,850
is very distinctive.

224
00:20:03,850 --> 00:20:04,770
You can have a try.

225
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:06,890
I don't need shoes. I'm just browsing.

226
00:20:07,730 --> 00:20:08,530
Give it a try.

227
00:20:09,450 --> 00:20:10,170
I really don't need shoes.

228
00:20:10,370 --> 00:20:11,010
Give it a try.

229
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:11,690
I really don't need it.

230
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:12,450
Just try it on.

231
00:20:20,770 --> 00:20:21,890
How is it? Good?

232
00:20:23,610 --> 00:20:24,250
Do you like it?

233
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:30,570
Yeah, it's good.

234
00:20:32,970 --> 00:20:33,610
I've tried.

235
00:20:34,130 --> 00:20:34,930
How much is it?

236
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:36,210
One thousand two hundred and five.

237
00:20:36,450 --> 00:20:37,490
We will have it.

238
00:20:38,410 --> 00:20:39,050
How much?

239
00:20:39,050 --> 00:20:39,850
One thousand two hundred and five.

240
00:20:40,890 --> 00:20:41,570
I don't want it.

241
00:20:41,970 --> 00:20:42,850
It's your big day.

242
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:43,890
I'll buy you a pair of shoes.

243
00:20:43,890 --> 00:20:44,770
I'm sure you'll need it.

244
00:20:47,290 --> 00:20:48,290
I really don't need it!

245
00:20:50,210 --> 00:20:50,810
Anran!

246
00:20:51,010 --> 00:20:51,930
I really don't need it.

247
00:21:00,690 --> 00:21:02,050
Are you free

248
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:02,930
on the 24th?

249
00:21:06,210 --> 00:21:07,330
Trial for the recommendation.

250
00:21:08,170 --> 00:21:09,210
I'll be free after that.

251
00:21:09,570 --> 00:21:10,730
Then let's go out.

252
00:21:12,050 --> 00:21:12,650
Sure.

253
00:21:16,570 --> 00:21:17,490
I'm leaving.

254
00:22:14,330 --> 00:22:15,370
Wenqin, you're back.

255
00:22:15,530 --> 00:22:16,150
Auntie.

256
00:22:20,850 --> 00:22:21,490
Father.

257
00:22:21,530 --> 00:22:22,210
I'm back.

258
00:22:23,610 --> 00:22:24,210
You're back.

259
00:22:32,450 --> 00:22:33,050
Wenqin.

260
00:22:34,330 --> 00:22:35,370
Did you have dinner?

261
00:22:36,970 --> 00:22:38,090
Don't forget to take the medicine.

262
00:22:45,770 --> 00:22:46,570
Tired?

263
00:22:49,810 --> 00:22:51,290
Are you preoccupied by some troubles?

264
00:22:52,370 --> 00:22:53,690
Did you get a girlfriend?

265
00:22:54,610 --> 00:22:55,250
Remember.

266
00:22:55,770 --> 00:22:57,730
Take her to eat something good.

267
00:22:59,770 --> 00:23:01,170
The diner at the alley entrance

268
00:23:01,410 --> 00:23:02,570
is fine.

269
00:23:03,690 --> 00:23:04,370
Dad.

270
00:23:06,690 --> 00:23:07,930
What kind of people

271
00:23:08,210 --> 00:23:08,890
buy cakes

272
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:09,970
for more than three hundred

273
00:23:10,770 --> 00:23:11,970
and buy a pair of shoes

274
00:23:12,410 --> 00:23:13,170
for over a thousand?

275
00:23:16,090 --> 00:23:16,730
Anyway,

276
00:23:17,570 --> 00:23:19,250
they are from a different kind of world.

277
00:23:20,970 --> 00:23:21,610
Wenqin.

278
00:23:24,810 --> 00:23:25,410
I need to

279
00:23:26,370 --> 00:23:27,250
discuss something with you.

280
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:30,730
In the Chinese New Year,

281
00:23:31,490 --> 00:23:33,290
I gave you 400 yuan of lucky money.

282
00:23:34,010 --> 00:23:34,690
Do you still have it?

283
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:35,890
I want to

284
00:23:36,210 --> 00:23:37,010
discuss with you.

285
00:23:38,210 --> 00:23:39,170
Lend me the money.

286
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:41,090
I'll pay for the medicine.

287
00:23:45,650 --> 00:23:46,450
No need to pay me back.

288
00:23:46,850 --> 00:23:47,610
Take medicine on time.

289
00:24:03,210 --> 00:24:04,490
I've saved money for a year.

290
00:24:05,370 --> 00:24:06,290
But I've spent it

291
00:24:06,850 --> 00:24:07,650
for only one cake.

292
00:24:15,370 --> 00:24:16,450
Liu Wenqin, come here.

293
00:24:17,570 --> 00:24:18,370
You guys go on.

294
00:24:23,210 --> 00:24:25,170
You have to prepare well for the 24th.

295
00:24:26,370 --> 00:24:27,850
This trial

296
00:24:27,850 --> 00:24:29,290
is not just about the school team.

297
00:24:29,770 --> 00:24:30,970
More importantly,

298
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:33,410
it will decide whether you will be recommended.

299
00:24:34,650 --> 00:24:35,330
Got it.

300
00:24:36,330 --> 00:24:37,410
In a good mood, huh?

301
00:24:37,890 --> 00:24:38,570
Yeah.

302
00:24:39,130 --> 00:24:40,050
What are you happy about?

303
00:24:40,690 --> 00:24:42,090
I asked him out on the 24th.

304
00:24:42,450 --> 00:24:43,970
What do you have in mind?

305
00:24:44,530 --> 00:24:46,250
I don't celebrate foreign festivals.

306
00:24:47,850 --> 00:24:48,610
Oh.

307
00:24:48,730 --> 00:24:50,250
What do you think I should give him as a present?

308
00:24:51,010 --> 00:24:51,650
You have

309
00:24:51,810 --> 00:24:53,530
bought him a pair of expensive shoes, right?

310
00:24:54,050 --> 00:24:54,810
It's worth it.

311
00:24:55,330 --> 00:24:56,690
He is very good at playing basketball.

312
00:24:57,210 --> 00:24:58,050
Don't give him anything.

313
00:24:58,810 --> 00:25:00,010
I'm not using your money.

314
00:25:01,090 --> 00:25:02,250
You don't know about boys.

315
00:25:02,810 --> 00:25:04,730
Is there anything wrong with buying him basketball shoes?

316
00:25:06,730 --> 00:25:07,970
Have you ever thought about this?

317
00:25:08,450 --> 00:25:10,050
If he wants to buy you a gift,

318
00:25:10,290 --> 00:25:11,170
what should he do?

319
00:25:15,890 --> 00:25:16,490
Bro.

320
00:25:18,650 --> 00:25:19,610
What do you think of me?

321
00:25:20,610 --> 00:25:21,210
In what way?

322
00:25:22,810 --> 00:25:24,930
Image, temperament and character.

323
00:25:27,650 --> 00:25:28,370
Actually,

324
00:25:29,490 --> 00:25:30,690
I think you are good.

325
00:25:33,930 --> 00:25:35,610
If a man like me

326
00:25:36,050 --> 00:25:37,330
wants to buy someone a gift,

327
00:25:37,890 --> 00:25:38,970
what do you think I should buy?

328
00:25:42,370 --> 00:25:43,010
Knife.

329
00:25:43,970 --> 00:25:44,570
Knife?

330
00:25:44,970 --> 00:25:46,050
It's manly to gift knives.

331
00:25:46,050 --> 00:25:47,130
What do you think?

332
00:25:51,730 --> 00:25:52,570
You're right.

333
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:56,690
I don't care about it.

334
00:25:57,650 --> 00:25:58,610
But he will.

335
00:26:02,410 --> 00:26:03,890
An empty-handed person

336
00:26:04,290 --> 00:26:05,650
get bewildered easily.

337
00:26:07,590 --> 00:26:08,250
It's true.

338
00:26:08,650 --> 00:26:10,850
Just gift him a handwritten card.

339
00:26:19,490 --> 00:26:20,650
They are not playing basketball,

340
00:26:20,850 --> 00:26:22,130
but fighting.

341
00:26:33,010 --> 00:26:34,330
That one on the court can't take it.

342
00:26:34,810 --> 00:26:36,010
Will you two play?

343
00:26:37,290 --> 00:26:38,210
One hundred and fifty yuan

344
00:26:38,410 --> 00:26:39,370
for a game.

345
00:26:39,370 --> 00:26:40,570
Will you two play?

346
00:27:47,730 --> 00:27:48,650
Why not blow a whistle!

347
00:28:25,890 --> 00:28:27,050
Easy, easy.

348
00:28:28,170 --> 00:28:30,050
Young people are indeed strong.

349
00:28:30,410 --> 00:28:31,250
Will you come tomorrow?

350
00:28:31,450 --> 00:28:33,050
I'll pay you two hundred for one game.

351
00:28:36,610 --> 00:28:37,230
Okay!

352
00:28:37,570 --> 00:28:39,250
I'll play as many games as you want.

353
00:28:39,290 --> 00:28:39,890
All right!

354
00:28:40,170 --> 00:28:40,770
Good.

355
00:28:55,250 --> 00:28:57,010
Why do you take part in that kind of game?

356
00:29:04,210 --> 00:29:05,330
You could be crippled.

357
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:07,050
Don't you want to go to college?

358
00:29:14,450 --> 00:29:15,050
Look.

359
00:29:21,890 --> 00:29:22,650
And look there.

360
00:29:27,650 --> 00:29:29,170
Don't you know the poem

361
00:29:29,170 --> 00:29:30,930
"Don't forget your ambitions when young.

362
00:29:32,650 --> 00:29:35,130
We were determined to be the best in the world."

363
00:30:46,450 --> 00:30:47,170
Is it good-looking?

364
00:30:48,190 --> 00:30:48,830
Yes.

365
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:51,450
If only

366
00:30:52,890 --> 00:30:54,410
it were true.

367
00:30:54,930 --> 00:30:57,050
There is no Santa Claus in this world.

368
00:30:59,010 --> 00:30:59,850
Yeah.

369
00:31:03,450 --> 00:31:04,370
Let me be your Santa Claus.

370
00:31:06,970 --> 00:31:07,690
Now?

371
00:31:09,610 --> 00:31:10,250
Next year.

372
00:31:13,170 --> 00:31:14,690
No matter what happens next year,

373
00:31:16,010 --> 00:31:16,730
and wherever you are,

374
00:31:17,290 --> 00:31:19,250
there will be a Santa Claus in front of you.

375
00:31:31,090 --> 00:31:32,890
Who makes a wish on Santa Claus?

376
00:31:33,970 --> 00:31:34,770
I don't care.

377
00:31:36,250 --> 00:31:37,050
What wish did you make?

378
00:31:38,490 --> 00:31:39,970
You are good at playing basketball.

379
00:31:40,370 --> 00:31:42,010
I want to go to the university you're recommended to.

380
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:47,370
Do you think it will come true?

381
00:31:57,370 --> 00:31:58,530
You're so good.

382
00:31:59,210 --> 00:32:00,930
Why are you going to the same college as me?

383
00:32:18,050 --> 00:32:18,730
How much is it?

384
00:32:19,250 --> 00:32:20,690
It's 1,280.

385
00:32:21,930 --> 00:32:23,250
This one is really good.

386
00:32:23,490 --> 00:32:24,210
The workmanship is fine

387
00:32:24,610 --> 00:32:25,730
and it's different from the rest.

388
00:32:26,090 --> 00:32:26,890
It's a limited edition.

389
00:32:27,050 --> 00:32:28,330
That's the only one left.

390
00:32:29,050 --> 00:32:30,050
It'd be a sincere gift

391
00:32:30,050 --> 00:32:30,890
for girls today.

392
00:32:34,450 --> 00:32:35,770
You don't close until night, do you?

393
00:32:36,030 --> 00:32:36,630
Yes.

394
00:32:37,210 --> 00:32:38,010
I don't have enough money with me.

395
00:32:38,050 --> 00:32:38,850
I'll come and buy it later.

396
00:32:38,890 --> 00:32:39,650
Keep it for me.

397
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:41,610
Okay, no problem. I'll wait for you.

398
00:32:43,850 --> 00:32:44,450
Brother Guang.

399
00:32:44,770 --> 00:32:45,610
Are there games today?

400
00:32:46,050 --> 00:32:46,690
Yes.

401
00:32:46,810 --> 00:32:47,810
There will be a game soon.

402
00:32:47,810 --> 00:32:48,610
Are you coming or not?

403
00:32:51,050 --> 00:32:52,210
Can you give 300 yuan for that?

404
00:32:53,490 --> 00:32:54,370
If you win,

405
00:32:54,370 --> 00:32:55,450
I'll give you four hundred.

406
00:32:56,770 --> 00:32:57,570
Thank you, Brother Guang.

407
00:32:57,610 --> 00:32:58,770
Okay, come soon.

408
00:33:29,410 --> 00:33:30,410
If you lose this game,

409
00:33:30,730 --> 00:33:31,610
I'm going to lose miserably!

410
00:33:32,050 --> 00:33:33,370
I'll make you suffer!

411
00:33:39,890 --> 00:33:40,530
If you really lose,

412
00:33:41,050 --> 00:33:41,890
you can't get a penny.

413
00:33:47,290 --> 00:33:48,330
You have to pay me all!

414
00:34:15,770 --> 00:34:17,090
Awesome!

415
00:34:22,770 --> 00:34:23,490
I'll buy

416
00:34:23,490 --> 00:34:24,130
this chain.

417
00:35:08,289 --> 00:35:09,410
Did you go to a fight?

418
00:35:10,690 --> 00:35:11,809
Normal training and playing

419
00:35:11,809 --> 00:35:13,090
won't make you injured like this!

420
00:35:13,729 --> 00:35:14,410
Tell me!

421
00:35:14,410 --> 00:35:15,809
How did you get these injuries!

422
00:35:17,090 --> 00:35:18,370
You're ruining your future!

423
00:35:18,570 --> 00:35:20,010
You disappointing brat!

424
00:35:39,530 --> 00:35:40,290
This is delicious.

425
00:35:46,050 --> 00:35:46,690
And this.

426
00:35:47,130 --> 00:35:47,730
Okay.

427
00:36:02,570 --> 00:36:03,250
Eat it.

428
00:36:13,890 --> 00:36:15,290
I have been very happy with you.

429
00:36:16,970 --> 00:36:18,170
Me, too.

430
00:36:28,570 --> 00:36:29,530
It's a holiday today.

431
00:36:32,730 --> 00:36:33,410
I...

432
00:36:34,050 --> 00:36:35,450
On this romantic and festive night,

433
00:36:35,850 --> 00:36:37,570
we have prepared some

434
00:36:37,610 --> 00:36:39,490
lucky draw for our guests.

435
00:36:40,130 --> 00:36:42,170
There will be five awards.

436
00:36:42,730 --> 00:36:43,890
Those who are lucky

437
00:36:43,930 --> 00:36:46,330
will get a little gift from us.

438
00:36:47,890 --> 00:36:49,570
Let's draw the fifth prize.

439
00:36:50,410 --> 00:36:51,410
Will we be so lucky?

440
00:36:51,410 --> 00:36:52,210
No. 16.

441
00:36:53,570 --> 00:36:54,410
No. 35.

442
00:36:56,410 --> 00:36:57,250
No. 24.

443
00:36:57,450 --> 00:36:58,690
We are No. 24.

444
00:36:59,330 --> 00:37:00,130
No. 17.

445
00:37:00,370 --> 00:37:00,990
Really!

446
00:37:02,190 --> 00:37:02,810
Hello.

447
00:37:05,390 --> 00:37:06,010
Thank you.

448
00:37:06,170 --> 00:37:07,170
Enjoy your meal.

449
00:37:07,330 --> 00:37:08,130
No. 8.

450
00:37:08,450 --> 00:37:09,410
What do you think it would be?

451
00:37:09,770 --> 00:37:10,650
Congratulations!

452
00:37:11,490 --> 00:37:12,370
Ten minutes later,

453
00:37:12,370 --> 00:37:14,810
we will draw the fourth prize.

454
00:37:15,650 --> 00:37:16,410
Is it good?

455
00:37:19,290 --> 00:37:20,290
Isn't it good?

456
00:37:24,230 --> 00:37:24,830
Yeah.

457
00:37:36,290 --> 00:37:36,930
Eat it.

458
00:37:39,730 --> 00:37:40,410
What's wrong?

459
00:37:44,450 --> 00:37:45,890
Don't you like seafood?

460
00:37:54,490 --> 00:37:55,370
Let me ask you.

461
00:37:56,970 --> 00:37:57,650
Do you think

462
00:37:59,130 --> 00:37:59,850
the river shrimp

463
00:38:01,330 --> 00:38:02,330
and the sea shrimp

464
00:38:02,330 --> 00:38:03,410
can live together?

465
00:38:04,770 --> 00:38:05,610
Of course not.

466
00:38:06,090 --> 00:38:07,730
They live in completely different environments.

467
00:38:08,050 --> 00:38:09,930
One in the sea and the other in the river.

468
00:38:13,330 --> 00:38:13,970
Got it.

469
00:38:17,090 --> 00:38:17,810
I'll go back now.

470
00:38:19,770 --> 00:38:20,890
A-are you all right?

471
00:38:22,950 --> 00:38:23,570
Yeah.

472
00:39:51,530 --> 00:39:52,130
Dad.

473
00:39:52,130 --> 00:39:52,850
I'm back.

474
00:39:54,090 --> 00:39:54,730
Kneel!

475
00:39:58,650 --> 00:40:00,290
Your coach called me

476
00:40:00,890 --> 00:40:02,530
and said you didn't get the quota.

477
00:40:11,690 --> 00:40:12,610
Liu Wenqin.

478
00:40:13,570 --> 00:40:15,690
Do you think our family can afford

479
00:40:15,770 --> 00:40:17,250
to let you go to a key high school?

480
00:40:19,090 --> 00:40:20,970
If you can't go to a key high school team,

481
00:40:21,730 --> 00:40:23,930
will you have a chance to play for the city team?

482
00:40:24,610 --> 00:40:26,090
If you can't make a name for yourself,

483
00:40:26,570 --> 00:40:27,930
you won't have a chance...

484
00:40:34,650 --> 00:40:36,050
You won't have a chance

485
00:40:37,370 --> 00:40:39,130
to walk out of this building!

486
00:40:40,530 --> 00:40:41,530
You won't have the chance

487
00:40:41,530 --> 00:40:42,130
to live

488
00:40:42,490 --> 00:40:44,930
a different life from this.

489
00:40:45,450 --> 00:40:48,170
Do you want to live in this corner all your life?

490
00:40:50,450 --> 00:40:52,170
I don't ask you to get ahead

491
00:40:52,530 --> 00:40:53,970
or make great achievements,

492
00:40:54,970 --> 00:40:57,650
I only want you to catch it when you have a chance!

493
00:41:01,370 --> 00:41:03,610
Why did you play pickup games to earn money?

494
00:41:04,570 --> 00:41:05,690
You are never

495
00:41:05,690 --> 00:41:07,730
a kid who likes money.

496
00:41:11,250 --> 00:41:11,890
If

497
00:41:14,210 --> 00:41:16,330
I had to start from the lowest,

498
00:41:17,130 --> 00:41:18,850
why did you give birth to me!

499
00:41:48,330 --> 00:41:49,530
Why are you following me?

500
00:41:50,090 --> 00:41:51,490
Why did you come to this crappy place?

501
00:41:51,490 --> 00:41:52,570
Get out of here! Get out!

502
00:41:52,570 --> 00:41:53,170
Get lost!

503
00:41:53,970 --> 00:41:54,570
I'm sorry.

504
00:41:55,290 --> 00:41:56,170
You looked strange.

505
00:41:56,250 --> 00:41:57,610
I just wanted to check.

506
00:42:01,850 --> 00:42:03,090
Don't follow me!

507
00:42:11,010 --> 00:42:11,890
But I have a gift

508
00:42:11,890 --> 00:42:13,050
that I haven't given you.

509
00:42:15,170 --> 00:42:15,810
You said it.

510
00:42:16,890 --> 00:42:17,770
The shrimp

511
00:42:18,410 --> 00:42:19,130
in the river can't live

512
00:42:19,130 --> 00:42:20,570
with those in the sea?

513
00:42:24,010 --> 00:42:25,170
Look at this place.

514
00:42:26,610 --> 00:42:28,290
We can't live together!

515
00:42:30,810 --> 00:42:31,770
What are you talking about?

516
00:42:32,890 --> 00:42:34,850
There's no such a big difference between us!

517
00:42:35,610 --> 00:42:36,250
If five years later

518
00:42:37,290 --> 00:42:37,970
or ten years later,

519
00:42:38,530 --> 00:42:39,450
I still live in this place,

520
00:42:39,450 --> 00:42:40,690
will you still say this?

521
00:42:43,250 --> 00:42:43,870
Yes.

522
00:42:46,370 --> 00:42:47,050
Don't be silly.

523
00:42:50,970 --> 00:42:51,770
Do you know

524
00:42:52,810 --> 00:42:54,170
the end point I struggle to get to

525
00:42:54,610 --> 00:42:55,890
can't even compare with your starting point!

526
00:43:00,610 --> 00:43:02,130
Then I will come back to be with you.

527
00:43:23,370 --> 00:43:24,690
Liu Wenqin.

528
00:44:20,570 --> 00:44:21,190
Qin.

529
00:44:22,130 --> 00:44:23,490
You suddenly dropped out of school.

530
00:44:24,130 --> 00:44:25,410
What are you going to do in the future?

531
00:44:27,970 --> 00:44:28,730
Earn money.

532
00:44:29,730 --> 00:44:30,810
Is money so important?

533
00:44:32,490 --> 00:44:33,730
Please take me with you!

534
00:44:34,570 --> 00:44:36,130
You should finish high school first.

535
00:44:36,730 --> 00:44:37,930
I'll go out and explore first.

536
00:44:40,650 --> 00:44:41,650
Then again,

537
00:44:42,810 --> 00:44:44,130
did you give her the necklace

538
00:44:44,210 --> 00:44:44,930
you bought?

539
00:44:45,770 --> 00:44:46,410
No.

540
00:44:46,410 --> 00:44:47,170
Why not?

541
00:44:49,330 --> 00:44:51,730
I've tried so hard to buy it.

542
00:44:53,290 --> 00:44:55,450
But it was just the fifth prize in the restaurant.

543
00:44:56,690 --> 00:44:57,890
That was a fancy restaurant.

544
00:44:57,930 --> 00:44:59,210
How coincidental!

545
00:44:59,370 --> 00:45:00,410
How silly!

546
00:45:09,770 --> 00:45:10,770
But

547
00:45:12,250 --> 00:45:14,170
what you give is different from theirs.

548
00:45:14,650 --> 00:45:15,530
What's the difference?

549
00:45:15,530 --> 00:45:16,570
It's with your feelings.

550
00:45:20,690 --> 00:45:21,330
But

551
00:45:25,890 --> 00:45:26,770
it's shameful.

552
00:45:35,970 --> 00:45:36,930
The stupidest thing is

553
00:45:38,970 --> 00:45:40,090
I promised her that

554
00:45:40,090 --> 00:45:40,890
next year,

555
00:45:40,890 --> 00:45:42,370
I'll play Santa Claus for her.

556
00:45:44,130 --> 00:45:45,210
Santa Claus?

557
00:45:48,370 --> 00:45:49,570
It's a little silly.

558
00:45:52,330 --> 00:45:53,450
Looks like I'll break my promise.

559
00:45:55,650 --> 00:45:56,730
People like us

560
00:45:57,490 --> 00:45:58,770
work so hard for her.

561
00:45:59,810 --> 00:46:01,610
But she can get those easily.

562
00:46:04,330 --> 00:46:05,370
We are men.

563
00:46:07,370 --> 00:46:08,010
What can we do about it?

564
00:46:09,690 --> 00:46:11,250
Seriously?

565
00:46:11,250 --> 00:46:13,330
I didn't know there was such a hard question in this world!

566
00:46:18,250 --> 00:46:18,970
One day,

567
00:46:20,690 --> 00:46:21,770
we will live in that place

568
00:46:24,850 --> 00:46:25,970
and live the best life!

569
00:46:28,570 --> 00:46:30,330
Live the best life!
